Toll Brothers Inc. (NYSE:TOL) Trading Volume Significantly Lower 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsToll Brothers Inc. (NYSE:TOL) Trading Volume Significantly Lower
July 25, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



Trading was light with 97K shares changing hands by the end of trading on Tuesday.  Shares saw a steep decrease in trading volume of 96.25% under the normal average daily volume. 
 There has been some selling insider activity on Toll Brothers Inc. (NYSE:TOL) recently.   Martin P. Connor, CFO disclosed the sale of 2,000 shares of TOL stock. The shares were sold on July 7th for an average price of $40.45. The CFO now owns $1,328,216 of the stock per the Form 4 SEC filing. CAO Joseph R. Sicree sold 4,500 shares at an average price of $38.50 on June 13th. Sicree now owns $876,530 of stock as reported to the SEC.
 Richard J. Braemer, Director sold $566,100 worth of shares at an average price of $37.74 on Thu the 8th. That brings Braemer’s holdings to $3,882,427 per an SEC filing yesterday.
 Here are some other firms who have updated their holdings.   Clear Harbor Asset Management, LLC trimmed its investment by selling 45,565 shares a decrease of 47.1% as of 06/30/2017. Clear Harbor Asset Management, LLC controls 51,265 shares valued at $2,036,000. The value of the position overall is down by 41.8%. Russell Investments Group, Ltd. downsized its position by shedding 227 shares a decrease of 25.0% in the quarter. Russell Investments Group, Ltd. owns 680 shares worth $27,000. The total value of its holdings decreased 18.2%.
 Acadian Asset Management LLC bolstered its stake by buying 24 shares an increase of 17.9% from 03/31/2017 to 06/30/2017. Acadian Asset Management LLC now holds 158 shares with a value of $6,000. The value of the position overall is up by 20.0%. First Citizens Bank & Trust Co added to its holdings by buying 2,951 shares an increase of 29.6%. First Citizens Bank & Trust Co currently owns 12,924 shares with a value of $511,000. The total value of its holdings increased 41.9%.
  On July 11 the stock rating was downgraded to “Underweight” from “Equalweight” in a report issued by Barclays. Mizuho began coverage of TOL with an initial rating of “Buy”.        Advertisement






 December 6 investment analysts at Deutsche Bank kept the stock rating at “Buy” but raised the price target  to $42.00 from $40.00. On December 5, 2016 Wedbush starting coverage on TOL with a rating of “Neutral”.
 Equity analyst Evercore ISI Group initiated coverage on the stock by announcing an initial rating of “Hold”. On September 29 analysts at Wells Fargo started coverage setting a rating of “Outperform”.
 The company is so far trading up by 1.48 percent from yesterday’s close.  Toll Brothers Inc. also announced a dividend for shareholders payable on Friday July 28th, 2017.  The dividend will be $0.080 per share for the quarter which comes to $0.32 on an annualized basis.  This dividend represents a yeild of $0.81 which is the dividend as a percentage of the current share price.  The ex-dividend date will be on Wednesday July 12th, 2017. 
 Company shares last traded at $39.79 barely above the 50 day moving average which is $39.04 and slightly over the 200 day moving average of $35.77.  The 50 day moving average went up by +1.92% and the 200 day average went up $4.02 or +11.25%. 
 The company currently has a P/E ratio of 16.41 and the market cap is 6.51B.  In the latest earnings report the EPS was $2.42 and is expected to be $3.15 for the current year with 163,574,000 shares currently outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is forecasted to be $1.32 and the next full year EPS is projected to be $3.48. 
 Toll Brothers, Inc., launched on May 28, 1986, is involved in designing, building, marketing, selling and arranging financing for detached and attached homes in luxury residential communities. The Company operates through two segments: Traditional Home Building and Toll Brothers City Living (City Living). Within the Traditional Home Building segment, it operates in five geographic segments in the United States: the North, consisting of Connecticut, Illinois, Massachusetts, Michigan, Minnesota, New Jersey and New York; the Mid-Atlantic, consisting of Delaware, Maryland, Pennsylvania and Virginia; the South, consisting of Florida, North Carolina and Texas; the West, consisting of Arizona, Colorado, Nevada and Washington, and California. City Living is the Business’s urban development division. Its products include Traditional Home Building Product and City Living Product. Its Traditional Home Building Product includes detached homes, move-up, executive, estate, and active-adult and age-qualified lines of home. Attached homes include flats townhouses/carriage homes, city living product, and active-adult and age-qualified line of homes. The Company operates its own land development, architectural, engineering, mortgage, title, landscaping, security monitoring, lumber distribution, house component assembly and manufacturing operations. As of October 31, 2016, the Company operated in 19 states..
